{
	"name": "Bolstered Bargainer",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/unholy/hands-circle-light-green.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Your pact came with some extra clauses that have provided you with useful capabilities. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>Your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p></li><li><p>You gain proficiency with your choice of the Arcana or Religion skill. If you are already proficient in both, choose one to gain an expertise die. You also learn a total of two skill specialties of the Arcana and/or Religion skills. They do not count against your skill specialties known. You must be proficient in the corresponding skill to take a skill specialty this way.</p></li><li><p>You learn a language of your choice from the following list: Abyssal, Aquan, Auran, Celestial, Draconic, Ignan, Infernal, Primordial, or Sylvan.</p></li><li><p>You gain an additional benefit based on your pact boon:</p><ul><li><p>If you have @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.6co2rqjh9npjg3eb]{Pact of the Blade}, you can choose one of the following options each time you summon it:</p><ul><li><p>If your pact weapon is a one-handed melee weapon you can summon a spectral @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.19oc64en7c6kmk1w]{medium} or @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.xy2bn4687azmkadw]{light shield} or a @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.sb8oo04tylbdb607]{dueling dagger} with it. You must have both hands free to summon both your pact weapon and the other item this way, and you cannot summon the other item without summoning your pact weapon. You are proficient with the summoned dueling dagger or shield. The item is made of semi-transparent magical energy and counts as magical, but has no other special bonuses or properties. The weapon or shield summoned this way vanishes if you let go of it.</p></li><li><p>If your pact weapon is a two-handed melee weapon, you gain temporary hit points equal to half your proficiency bonus at the beginning of each of your turns while wielding it.</p></li><li><p>If your pact weapon is a melee weapon with the versatile property, you can choose either the one-handed or two-handed options when summoning it.</p></li><li><p>If your pact weapon is a ranged weapon, it magically generates ammunition when you fire it. Ammunition created this way counts as magical but has no other special properties, vanishes immediately after hitting or missing, and cannot be given to anyone else or used in any other weapon (it vanishes if you try).</p></li></ul></li><li><p>If you have @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.f2mfiz8spijbzs6h]{Pact of the Chain}, your familiar can also be in the form of a creature of small or medium size. You cannot choose creatures of the Humanoid or Giant types for this benefit.</p></li><li><p>If you have @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.f2mfiz8spijbzs6h]{Pact of the Tome}, choose a second warlock expanded spell list. Also, choose a 1st or 2nd spell from one of your expanded spell lists. You learn that spell and it does not count against your warlock spells known.</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
